          "text": "Hospital Course"
        },
        "valueString": "The patient was a 44-year-old man diagnosed with Ebstein's anomaly resulting in severe right atrial and right ventricular dilatation with right moderate ventricular dysfunction and severe tricuspid regurgitation. The patient also suffered from HIV immunodeficiency with previous cerebral infection and Kaposi's Sarcoma. In the post-operative period, the patient developed severe right ventricular dysfunction with LCOS, which required ECMO support."
      }
